      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SCOTCH YOU (6) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fifth (20.09) last time in a Grade 4/5 at Capalaba. Has a good record here at this journey. Can atone. REDMAN JOHNNY (1) doesn't win out of turn. Finished in the minors latest when second (19.92) at this track and may be close to breaking through. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Leading chance. MULLIGRUB (7) is a talented type and proved too strong last time to win by 2.75 lengths at this track in a handy 19.71 beating TOP EIGHT. Winner at his latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Has hit winning form and can go on with it. DING DING HARROW (2) placed here at this trip last start - cannot be ignored.",
